 Silver medallist at the 2018 Commonwealth Games Faith Obazuaye and African champions  Isau Ogunkunle as well as Tajudeen Agunbiade are among the top stars confirmed for the second edition of the annual Valuejet Para Table Tennis Open. The tourney begins on December 19 at the Molade Okoya-Thomas Hall of Teslim Balogun Stadium. Already 100 of players across the country are already in Lagos for the three-day championship organised by Sunday Odebode Foundation in collaboration with the Nigeria Table Tennis Federation (NTTF). Obazuaye, Ogunkunle and Agunbiade are among the Tokyo 2021 Paralympic Games-bound athletes already in the second phase of camping for Tokyo. According to the coordinator of the tournament Sunday Odebode, this year’s would be staged nationally with players aiming to be part of the national team eager to be part of the competition. “We are grateful to our sponsor – Valuejet Airline who have decided to keep faith with the staging of the competition despite the challenges of  COVID-19, we will be staging this year nationally with the hope that new players will emerge this year. But we will ensure that we follow the laid-down COVID-19 protocols,” he said. Odebode, however, said that the tournament is expected to also  help the players to shape up for the 2021 National Sports Festival in Benin City, the Edo State capital while Tokyo-bound Paralympians would also be using the tournament as a tune-up to the biggest sporting event in Japan.